He is also an Eagle Scout.\n\nAfter graduation in December 2014, Chase aspires to begin his career as a production forester with the Weyerhaeuser Company \u2013 a diverse company involved in nearly every facet of the forest products industry, from growing and harvesting trees to producing products that are fundamental to human needs. He has worked with the company the past two summers in Natchitoches, Louisiana and Broken Bow, Oklahoma.\n\nChase has done a superb job of recruiting for our Corps throughout his time as a cadet and especially as Commander of the Darling Recruiting Company. His countless hours dedicated to growing and sustaining the Corps have been invaluable, and he certainly sets the bar high for those cadets who will follow in his footsteps. He is a very proud and honorable representative of our Corps, and he truly inspires young men and women to want to join the Corps.
